casebody.data:
PEOPLE of the State of Michigan, Plaintiff-Appellee,
v.
Joe MALDONADO, Jr., Defendant-Appellant. SC: 158467
COA: 343218 Supreme Court of Michigan. March 5, 2019

Order

On order of the Court, the motion for immediate consideration is GRANTED.

The application for leave to appeal the August 9, 2018 order of the Court of Appeals is considered, and it is DENIED, because we are not persuaded that the questions presented should be reviewed by this Court. The defendant remains entitled to file a motion for relief from judgment under MCR subchapter 6.500.
